quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  18,94,"They said, ",footnotes:1:Savage tribes who had ravaged large parts of central Asia, committing every kind of atrocity.
  18,95,"He said, "
  18,96,"Bring me bars of iron"
  19,55,"And he used to enjoin on his people prayer and zakāh and was to his Lord pleasing [i.e., accepted by Him]."
  19,56,"And mention in the Book, Idrees. Indeed, he was a man of truth and a prophet."
  19,57,"And We raised him to a high station."
  20,37,"And We had already conferred favor upon you another time,"
  20,38,"When We inspired to your mother what We inspired,"
  20,39,"[Saying], 'Cast him into the chest and cast it into the river, and the river will throw it onto the bank; there will take him an enemy to Me and an enemy to him.' And I bestowed upon you love from Me{1} that you would be brought up under My eye [i.e., observation and care].",footnotes:1:Allāh put love of Moses into the hearts of the people.
  21,13,"[Some angels said], ",footnotes:1:About what happened to you.  This is said to them in sarcasm and ridicule.
  21,14,"They said, "
  21,15,"And that declaration of theirs did not cease until We made them [as] a harvest [mowed down], extinguished [like a fire]."